---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Now" description="What Parker is currently building, learning, and thinking about.">
  <main class="now-main">

    <header class="now-header">
      <p class="label" style="color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Now</p>
      <h1>What I'm doing now</h1>
      <p class="now-updated label">Updated June 2026 · Melbourne, FL</p>
    </header>

    <div class="now-body">

      <section class="now-section">
        <h2>Building</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>nuclear-pf</strong> — investigating whether SMRs can remain competitive with solar on the question of financing structure, not technology cost. Writing a paper on it with Liam Barney. ANS Winter 2026 abstract submitted. The argument: the same reactor, at the same cost, can be financially viable or impossible depending entirely on the instruments around it.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>SmartSignals</strong> — MCAP sensor data pipeline for urban traffic validation. Currently building pairwise distance analysis and closest-approach detection for vulnerable road users (cyclists, pedestrians) in the Aerospace Systems Lab under Dr. Nguyen.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>This website.</strong>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="now-section">
        <h2>Studying</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Full-time aerospace engineering student at Florida Tech. Coursework this term includes [add your courses]. The classroom and the lab are increasingly hard to separate — which feels right.</li>
          <li>Nuclear project finance — LPO loan structure, IRA production tax credit mechanics, offtake agreements, and why Vogtle failed where Crane/TMI succeeded.</li>
          <li>ROS Noetic + Foxglove Studio for the SmartSignals pipeline.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="now-section">
        <h2>Training</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Running. Half marathon in November. Building the weekly mileage slowly — trying not to wreck my knees before the race.</li>
          <li>Fundraising for the <a href="https://fundraisers.hakuapp.com/parker-abrantes" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-link">Emily Whitehead Foundation</a> as part of it. Emily Whitehead was the first pediatric patient to receive CAR-T cell therapy and is now over a decade in remission. The run means something.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="now-section">
        <h2>Reading</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><em>Thinking, Fast and Slow</em> — Daniel Kahneman. The chapter on substitution questions changed how I read my own reasoning.</li>
          <li><em>Atomic Habits</em> — James Clear. Less about the system, more about using it as a mirror for what I'm actually building toward.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="now-section">
        <h2>Writing About</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Theory of mind — how we model other people's inner states, and what it costs us when we get it wrong.</li>
          <li>Life beyond and entrapped in work — what it means to be ambitious and also present.</li>
          <li>Identity and becoming — documenting life as we build it, not after the fact.</li>
          <li>Essays go to <a href="https://parkerabrantes.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-link">Ground Control on Substack</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="now-section">
        <h2>Looking For</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Summer 2027 internships in nuclear energy, energy finance, systems engineering, or technical program management.</li>
          <li>Conversations with people building things that matter — especially at the intersection of energy policy and engineering reality.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="now-footer">
      <p class="label" style="color: var(--muted);">
        This is a <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: var(--dim);">now page</a>.
        Updated manually when things change.
      </p>
    </div>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .now-main {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 8rem 2rem 6rem;
  }

  .now-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .now-updated {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .now-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }

  .now-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .now-section ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .now-section li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--dim);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .now-section li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .inline-link {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .now-footer {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
</style>
